Sometimes it comes to my mind, how many lives we live in our lifetime. Everyday is different and with every new day we experience one new personality of ourselves. ✨
It's difficult to explain how we evolve and grow with each passing day but we all realise it at some point that this growth is essential. 
When we look behind, we all have come very far from what we were and what we are now. And maybe it's all not positive but we've all grown beautifully in our own way. 💚

latestPosts.caption:
It’s not about talking every day.
It’s about showing up when it matters most.
To the friendships that feel like home — no matter the distance, no matter the time. 💛

Tag your soul friends who are always there — even from miles away. 🫶✨

#LongDistanceFriendship #FriendshipGoals #RealConnections #FriendsWhoAreFamily #HeartfeltBonds #EmotionalReel #SupportSystem #TrueFriendship #AlwaysThereForYou #FriendshipMatters #ForeverFriends

*SAKHI*
Sakhi – a word that means friend, but to me, it means home.🏠 

There’s something so sacred about female friendships — a quiet, unshakeable bond that sees you through heartbreaks, celebrations, everyday chaos, and the silence in between. 💌

I cherish the women in my life who have stood by me not just when I’ve shined, but when I’ve crumbled. They’ve seen me undone, and never once flinched. There’s a language only we understand — made of shared glances, unspoken understanding, and laughter that feels like healing.🫶🏻

With them, I don’t need to be perfect. I just need to be me.
And when I’m with them, I bloom.
It’s rare. It’s real. It’s peace.✨

Here’s to the women who become your mirror, your strength, your safe place.
May we always hold space for each other like this.
May we never forget the power of a Sakhi.📸💅🏻
